          "article": "Zoho Billing added support for Zoho MCP, letting AI assistants interact with billing workflows, according to the [Zoho Billing blog](https://www.zoho.com/blog/billing/zoho-billing-mcp.html).\n\nThe important part is the workflow scope: teams can query billing data, create invoices, generate payment links, and flag renewal risk from assistants such as ChatGPT, Claude, or Gemini. That makes Zoho Billing part of the emerging agent-access layer for finance operations.\n\n- Buyer signal: Relevant for finance teams that want AI assistants to work with billing data while staying inside a governed vendor-supported setup.\n- Follow-up: Review authentication, permissions, audit logs, write-action safeguards, and how Zoho prevents assistants from taking unintended billing actions."
