          "sourceNote": "Official Zoho Billing changelog with dated feature behavior.",
          "article": "Zoho Billing added Restrict Overage for drawdown add-ons, as listed in Zoho's [What's New](https://www.zoho.com/us/billing/whats-new.html) changelog.\n\nThis is a practical control for usage-based or prepaid-credit businesses. If customers buy a credit pool or drawdown allowance, the billing system needs to prevent consumption from exceeding the purchased allocation unless the business explicitly allows it.\n\n- Buyer signal: Useful for companies selling prepaid usage, credits, or controlled entitlements.\n- Follow-up: Test how restrictions behave across renewals, top-ups, mid-cycle changes, failed payments, and customer-facing usage notifications."
