      "status": "accepted",
      "sourceNote": "Official product update post with feature-level detail.",
      "article": "Maxio's [June 2026 product update](https://www.maxio.com/blog/maxio-june-2026-product-updates) bundles several revenue-operations improvements across metering, ARPU reporting, integrations, and proration behavior.\n\nThe bigger story is that Maxio is tightening the operational layer around usage-based and hybrid billing. Metering affects whether usage becomes billable cleanly, ARPU affects how finance reads expansion, integrations affect handoff to CRM and accounting, and proration affects invoice trust when plans change mid-cycle.\n\n- Buyer signal: Good fit evidence for SaaS and AI companies that care about billing accuracy, revenue metrics, and operational handoffs.\n- Follow-up: Validate how each update behaves under real contract changes, multi-currency accounts, CRM sync, and accounting close workflows.",
