      "article": "Sage and PwC announced an [agentic AI delivery model](https://www.sage.com/en-us/news/press-releases/2026/04/sage-and-pwc-use-agentic-ai-to-get-sage-intacct-finance-teams-up-and-running-faster/) for Sage Intacct implementations.\n\nThis is buyer-relevant because ERP implementation risk is often more important than feature checklists. If the delivery model can improve consistency, setup speed, or migration quality, it may reduce time-to-value for finance teams. The practical question is whether the AI-assisted approach changes outcomes, not just whether it sounds modern.\n\n- Buyer signal: Implementation acceleration is a real selection factor for finance buyers comparing ERP and accounting platforms.\n- Follow-up: Ask for proof points on deployment time, data migration quality, controls, partner responsibilities, and post-launch support.",
